JOB TITLE
Business Data Analyst, Investment Analytics, Investment Operations & Applications Branch

REPORTING TO

Team Leader, Investment Data Analysis

SCOPE OF POSITION

The Business Data Analyst’s primary focus within the Investment Operations & Applications Branch is to ensure all applications and tools have the complete information required for business users on a daily basis. The daily cycle of all investment systems are monitored to ensure data integrity and availability within the Investment applications. Additionally, the role requires qualitative checks and controls being assessed as it relates to investment data management. The role will also participate in investment system upgrades and implementations. The position requires strong analytical skills coupled with investment operations knowledge including pricing and setup of securities and systems implementation experience. Strong knowledge with investment instrument security characteristics including bonds, equities and... derivative products such as options, swaps and futures.

RESPONSIBILITIES
• Ensures the quality of the security master records across investment systems such as trading, portfolio management, data warehouse and analytics;
• Ensure the timeliness and completeness of daily data feeds from several internal/external sources;
• Validates the quality of the data fed into the various investment applications including portfolio management, data warehouse & performance & risk analytics tools;
• Creates data integrity reporting to assess potential data issues resident in the various Investment applications;
• Develops naming conventions and definitional standards for data and reports and monitors adherence to the standards;
• Performs business & data analysis in order to resolve data issues with vendors and Investment business areas;
• Reviews various system error logging in order to assess the corrections required;
• Reconciles data as required to various sources to assess quality;
• Validates and reviews securities pricing methodologies to ensure calculations;
• Provides problem solving, troubleshooting of issues and consulting support for analytics systems functions and data supplier issues;
• Provides support to users in the development of new reports and in the resolution of reporting and other data issues;
• Provides end-user support for the Investment applications including the development of new reports and system interfaces, training, general problem solving and process improvements;
• Participates in the investment systems upgrades including data conversion, testing and implementation;
• Share joint responsibility for enabling the project team to effectively execute work activities in order to achieve project goals and objectives;
• Develop a strong proficiency with the computer applications being utilized for the Investment business (Portia, CRD, PACE, Bloomberg, Barra etc.);
• Develop and maintain an understanding of investment products and customer needs in order to respond quickly and accurately to questions and problems that arise;
• Develop effective working relationships with investment management and operations, custodians, auditors, system vendors and others in the industry.

QUALIFICATIONS
• Knowledge of investment management principles and practices with exposure to marketable securities including derivatives.
• Knowledge of investment data uses for security master characteristics, corporate actions, risk analytics etc
• Knowledge of investment instrument pricing attributes.
• Experience working within an Investment operations environment, back and/or middle office and/or in an investment and financial systems administration, implementation and reporting.
• Highly analytical with strong consulting and problem solving ability.
• Proactive and results oriented with good time management skills and the ability to work well under pressure and focus on multiple tasks concurrently.
• A team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills.
• Minimum education: Post secondary training in finance including University degree in Mathematics, Commerce & Finance or equivalent experience. Enrolment in CGA, CMA or CFA preferred. Completion of Canadian Securities Course an asset.
• Experience with ODBC report writers such as Crystal, Access etc required. Experience with SQL queries.
• Working knowledge of MS Office including excel spreadsheets with real time links and access databases.
• Demonstrated aptitude for analysis and problem solving.
• Ability to multi-task effectively in fast-paced, multiple project environments.
• Excellent interpersonal and communication (written and verbal) skills are essential to deal with all levels of staff and outside contacts

The Data Analyst will be responsible for processing, designing, and presenting solutions to help OEG Retail Cannabis with data driven decision making. The Data Analyst will work with subject matter experts as well as business and operational leaders to determine requirements, define key performance indicators and develop solutions to provide insights for business problems. Through the collection, examination, and analysis of complex data you will ensure that the insights are understood by all stakeholders to drive results.

Your Focus in this Role:
• Work with modern data platforms
• Generate recurring reports on an established schedule and distribute to stakeholders
• Conduct regular reviews of reports in publication and reassess business need
• Work with departments within the organization to understand their business and enable effective solution design
• Develop data solutions that provide mission-critical information to our internal customers
• Design and develop data... visualization solutions that present impactful information
• Design and develop data engineering solutions (data virtualization, ETL/ELT) to make data available for a wide range of analytical uses
• Lead workshops with internal customers to capture requirements and translate them into solution designs
• Respond to ad-hoc data requests within the organization in a timely manner
• Educate/train cross-functional staff members on optimal use of systems and data solutions
• Offer support by responding to data problems in a timely manner
• Support the creation, review, and maintenance of framework, policy, and procedure documentation relating to Data Quality
• Collaborate with corporate BI team to develop and implement a Data Governance process
• Participate in project teams as required and collaborate as a team to deliver business outcomes
• Proactively monitor and respond to database alerts or issues
• Research technical problems, analyze business requirements, evaluate alternative design approaches and technical design processes to meet business requirements
• Collaborate with Corporate BI team to design and implement conceptual, logical and physical data models to continue to evolve OEG Retail Cannabis database solutions
• Have the opportunity to develop your problem solving and leadership skills
• Help shape the future of our Data and Analytics practices

Who You Are:
• You take an open, collaborative, positive-minded approach to professional tech work;
• You have a curious, proactive mindset and ability to work effectively on teams of various sizes;
• You have the ability to deliver presentations on focused topics to both technical and non-technical audiences;
• You are proficient in data management best practices and principles;
• You have strong communication skills with the ability to work in a consultative role with various stakeholders;
• You have a talent for building great working relationships at all levels within an organization

Education, Experience and Skills:
• 3+ years of professional development experience;
• A degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, Commerce, or equivalent diploma;
• Significant experience designing and implementing data visualization solutions in Power BI;
• Significant fluency in SQL;
• Experience working in a data warehousing function, including experience with data warehousing tools, technologies and approaches;
• Proficiency in Microsoft Azure and AWS BI technologies is a strong asset;
• Designing and implementing ETL/ELT processes is a strong asset

About the Company

Our client is a healthcare provider. They are looking for a full-time Reporting & Analytics Specialist.

Why Work Here
• Be a part of one of Toronto's largest healthcare providers
• Work in a collaborative team environment and provide thoughtful analytics to help drive the business forward

About the Opportunity

Data Analytics & Governance
• Obtains and facilitates understanding of clinical and business systems, including processes and data flows, interfaces and integration necessary to facilitate analytical outputs;
• Collects, analyzes, and interprets large and complex clinical, financial, supply chain, and human resources data sets to identify trends, patterns, and insights;
• Reviews the accuracy, completeness, and consistency of data sources by ensuring quality controls are in place and performing data audits where required;
• Develops predictive models and perform statistical analysis to report on past performance, report on future performance, and identify... opportunities for operational improvement;
• Collaborates with the Business Transformation team to develop and recommend business transformation and process improvement objectives where required, including root cause analysis of process gaps, review of transactions, offering recommendations and implementing improvements, and providing the groundwork for business maintenance of new processes;
• Collaborates with the Data Governance team to advance data governance initiatives where required, including understanding of data structures and cleansing for increased consistency and reliability for subsequent analytical work and reporting;
• Automates data extraction, transformation, and loading processes to streamline reporting and enhance data accuracy and integrity.

Reporting & Customer Service
• Collaborates with clinical, business, and governance stakeholders to obtain an understanding of the risks and objectives informing reporting and analytical requests;
• Gathers and develops reporting requirements from the applicable clinical, business, and governance stakeholders and works with R&A leadership to prioritize requests;
• Collaborates with internal and external stakeholders and colleagues to establish metrics and benchmarks for measuring business performance;
• Designs and develops visually appealing and interactive dashboards, reports, and presentations to effectively communicate key insights to stakeholders;
• Develops automated data extraction and reporting to facilitate increased “self-serve” and “core” reporting tools and increased capacity for analysis and insight by other teams;
• Communicates findings and insights to stakeholders in a clear and concise manner, and facilitate data-driven discussions to support decision-making processes;
• Resolves complex and escalated operational issues including mediation with impacted stakeholders where necessary;
• Develops and maintains relationships with a broad array of stakeholders, using effective communication and influencing skills to gain support for recommended initiatives;
• Advances personal learning and professional development in matters, best practices, emerging areas and standards in a number of cross-functional areas impacting the hospital, including finance, supply chain, HR/payroll compliance, and clinical operations.

About You
• CPA (CFA/MBA) or close to
• Hybrid (FR/Analysis) experience

Salary Range

$85,000 - $100,000/year

How to Apply

Click the “Apply Now” button and follow the instructions to submit your resume. Please know that we only accept documents in MS Word or Rich Text formats.

When referencing this job, quote #390818

You must currently reside within the Greater Toronto Area and be permitted to work in Canada to be considered for this opportunity. A recruiter will be in touch with you if your profile meets our client’s requirements for this role
